&#8220;Harry Potter and the Cursed Child&#8221; has bagged a record-breaking 11 nominations for the 2017 Olivier Awards.The news makes the West End show the most-nominated new play in history, Variety reports.The spinoff of J.K. Rowling&#8217;s world-famous wizarding franchise was nominated for Best Director,&#8217; Best Actor,&#8217; Best Costume Design&#8217; and Outstanding Achievement in Music,&#8217; among others.The winners will be revealed on Sunday, April 9 in London. For the full list of nominees, see http://www.olivierawards.com/nominations/by-show/-Relaxnews